      "answer": "The theory of relativity, developed by Albert Einstein in the early twentieth century, revolutionized the understanding of space, time, and gravitation. It is divided into two parts:\n\n*   **Special relativity:** Published in 1905, it addresses objects moving at constant velocities, establishes that the speed of light is constant in all inertial frames, and states that the laws of physics are identical for all non-accelerating observers. It also introduced the mass-energy equivalence (E=mc\u00b2), showing that mass and energy are interconvertible.\n*   **General relativity:** Published in 1915, it extends the framework to non-inertial reference frames and describes gravity as the curvature of spacetime caused by mass and energy.",
