      "answer": "The fall of the Roman Empire is attributed to a combination of the following factors:\n\n*   **Internal and Political Issues:** Internal instability, the gradual erosion of central authority, frequent civil wars, political fragmentation, and the administrative split into the Eastern and Western Roman Empires.\n*   **Economic and Military Issues:** Economic hardship, economic decline, economic stagnation, military overstretch, military overextension, and a series of costly military campaigns.\n*   **External Pressures:** Pressures from migrating peoples, including barbarian migrations and specific migrating tribes such as the Goths and Vandals.\n\nThe Western Roman Empire specifically fell in 476 CE (or 476 AD) when the last emperor, Romulus Augustulus, was deposed by the Germanic chieftain Odoacer.",
